<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Being a road warrior what bites my arse about the new specs is the fact that my laptop will *never* be able to play Luclin.  My desktop won't have a problem, but my laptop barely handled the increased graphics requirement of SoV.

I love great graphics, but half of my play time in EQ is done in the middle of no-where in a hotel.  EQ gives me something to do other than burning my last 2 braincells down in the bar.

Verant has always ignored the fact that a good 5-10% of it's user base are laptop users.  Call their support and tell them you are on a laptop and they'll give you the standard "EQ wasn't designed for laptops, goodbye."  

I just hope this upgrade doesn't prevent me from playing Kunark/old world while on the road.

